Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
cutBoxListFromPowerDomain(25.10)              cutBoxListFromPowerDomain(25.10)

Name
       cutBoxListFromPowerDomain  - Cuts out default power domains from a non-
       default power domain

Syntax
       cutBoxListFromPowerDomain

       [-help]

       -powerdomain <powerDomainName>

       -boxList {{box1} ...}

       Cuts out default power domains from a non-default  power  domain.  This
       command is mainly used to solve buffering related issues.

       Use  this  command  with  other  commands like ecoAddRepeater to insert
       buffers in the cutout box.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each cutBoxListFromPowerDomain parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man cutBoxListFromPowerDomain

       -powerDomain
              Specifies the Power Domain in which you want to cut out.

       -boxList
              Specifies the list of boxes to be cut.

Examples
       cutBoxListFromPowerDomain    -powerDomain   pd   -boxList   {   {list1}
       {list2}......}

       The list is numbers in the format: {llx1 lly1 urx1 ury1}

       cutBoxListFromPowerDomain -powerDomain 1.0V_Domain \

       -boxList {{10 10 20 20} {35 60 45 70}}

       This  will  cut  box  {10  10  20 20} and {35 60 45 70} from the domain
       1.0V_Domain, and these two boxes will become the default domain.

